post_text: Due to the continued threat of COVID-19, Governor Mike DeWine will not be reopening schools for the remainder of this school year. While we greatly miss having our students in the buildings, Evergreen Local Schools will continue remote learning for all students in grades K-12. Friday’s superintendent update will include more information on the continued closure. Let’s finish strong Vikings, we only have a little more than four weeks to go!

It has been brought to our attention that some families are not receiving emails from Evergreen Local Schools. If this is the case, please note the following:

• Be sure to check your spam folders and allow these messages to be delivered to your inboxes.
• Check that you have not blocked emails from Evergreen Local Schools. Please unblock us; this will allow Evergreen messages to arrive in your inbox.
• There is a chance that your email is not in the District’s alert system. Your email may have changed or it may not have been shared with the District during the annual registration period. Please submit your email on the Email Verification form by clicking the link or visiting the Coronavirus Information page on the Evergreen website.

https://forms.gle/54izbZfDGwMgoDie8

Hello Students!
We miss our Vikings! We know this is a complicated time in your world, and unfortunately, there are currently more questions than there are answers. Rest assured, we are working diligently to provide you with online lessons and support if the mandated school closure is continued. We will hopefully also have answers as to which spring events we will be able to host as soon as possible. Thank you for your patience. Be kind to yourself and one another.

post_text: The Regional Boys Basketball Championship Game scheduled for 7pm Saturday at BGSU’s Stroh Center will continue to allow only limited spectator attendance following recommendations from Governor Dewine and OHSAA. Only those who were permitted to attend Wednesday evening’s game will be permitted to attend the Regional Championship game on Saturday night. If you attended Wednesday’s game and are unable to attend Saturday’s game, please notify the High School main office so we’re able to redistribute your ticket. Changes in the approved ticket holder must be pre-approved by the HS office before Saturday. We appreciate your cooperation and go Vikings!

post_text:
Beginning in January the 4th graders of Evergreen Elementary participated in the United Way Crunch Out Obesity program. This program provided all of our 4th graders an exercise ball and equipment to take home. All of the students were given instruction as well as programming to be successful using their new exercise balls. Also, there was a contest to motivate students. Pictured are the winners of this years program for Evergreen Elementary:
Overall Winner: Peyton Mossing
Classroom Winners: Izzy Bonaminio, Lexi Johnson, Zoey Schwen

post_text: The OHSAA has ruled that in an effort to help slow the spread of COVID-19. Only essential personnel and select family members will be allowed to attend this week’s tournament games. Unfortunately, this includes Evergreen’s regional boys basketball games at BGSU’s Stroh Center. At this time, all presale tickets are void. For reimbursement purposes, we ask that you please keep your voided presale tickets. Voided presale tickets will be required for reimbursement. Evergreen Staff will be available in the main office of the high school from 8am - 3pm throughout the week to facilitate presale ticket refunds.
